00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.670 align:middle line:84%
>> We're all familiar with the
illusion that objects made out

00:00:12.670 --> 00:00:16.420 align:middle line:84%
of matter appear to be
distinct and separate entities.

00:00:16.420 --> 00:00:19.330 align:middle line:84%
In contrast, quantum
physics emphasizes

00:00:19.330 --> 00:00:21.730 align:middle line:84%
that everything is
entangled, forming

00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:24.280 align:middle line:90%
a whole, or singularity.

00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:29.830 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible we live
in an entangled universe?

00:00:29.830 --> 00:00:31.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm your host, Bruce
Lipton, for this series

00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:33.887 align:middle line:90%
on inner revolution.

00:00:33.887 --> 00:00:37.296 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:37.296 --> 00:00:46.570 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.570 --> 00:00:48.180 align:middle line:84%
To visualize how
what we perceive

00:00:48.180 --> 00:00:51.180 align:middle line:84%
as matter is influenced
by energy fields,

00:00:51.180 --> 00:00:54.420 align:middle line:84%
we must first understand
how energy waves entangle

00:00:54.420 --> 00:00:57.360 align:middle line:84%
and generate constructive
and destructive interference

00:00:57.360 --> 00:01:00.270 align:middle line:84%
patterns that influence the
character of the material

00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:01.860 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:04.590 align:middle line:84%
Both quantum physics
and the new biology

00:01:04.590 --> 00:01:07.710 align:middle line:84%
emphasize the influence of
the mind's energy field,

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:13.710 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, as fundamental
in shaping our life experiences.

00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.770 align:middle line:84%
In previous episodes, we
provided a simple formula

00:01:16.770 --> 00:01:18.200 align:middle line:90%
for the nature of life.

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:23.170 align:middle line:84%
And that is protein plus
signal equals behavior.

00:01:23.170 --> 00:01:26.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, the issue is we know
what the proteins are.

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:29.070 align:middle line:84%
But what kind of
signals are used

00:01:29.070 --> 00:01:32.130 align:middle line:84%
in creating the life
that we experience?

00:01:32.130 --> 00:01:35.250 align:middle line:84%
Well, conventional science
and conventional medicine,

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:38.010 align:middle line:84%
allopathic medicine,
employs the idea

00:01:38.010 --> 00:01:39.870 align:middle line:84%
that the body is a
physical mechanism

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:42.390 align:middle line:84%
and can only respond
to physical signals,

00:01:42.390 --> 00:01:45.940 align:middle line:84%
hence the use of
pharmaceuticals and drugs.

00:01:45.940 --> 00:01:48.570 align:middle line:84%
However, there is
a new understanding

00:01:48.570 --> 00:01:50.970 align:middle line:84%
that completely changes
our belief system,

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:55.980 align:middle line:84%
because quantum physics
reveals that energy is really

00:01:55.980 --> 00:01:58.300 align:middle line:90%
the source of everything.

00:01:58.300 --> 00:02:00.960 align:middle line:84%
And so looking at the
body as a physical entity

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:84%
is actually an illusion,
an incorrect understanding.

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, when we talk
about energy, we

00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:10.740 align:middle line:84%
can actually define it using
two different characteristics

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:11.700 align:middle line:90%
of energy.

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:15.870 align:middle line:84%
One is force and
one is information.

00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:18.420 align:middle line:84%
Energy as a force,
for example, is

00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:20.670 align:middle line:90%
what is used to drive our car.

00:02:20.670 --> 00:02:24.240 align:middle line:84%
Energy is a force
that creates movement.

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:27.960 align:middle line:84%
And this is the force
that medicine actually

00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:32.940 align:middle line:84%
considers energy that influences
physical matter by disturbing

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:33.960 align:middle line:90%
it.

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:36.330 align:middle line:90%
This is called ionizing energy.

00:02:36.330 --> 00:02:38.430 align:middle line:84%
It's energy like UV
light from the sun when

00:02:38.430 --> 00:02:42.240 align:middle line:84%
you get a sunburn or x-rays
when too many x-rays actually

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:43.680 align:middle line:90%
can burn the tissue.

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:46.500 align:middle line:84%
Then these energies
become part of the realm

00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:49.380 align:middle line:84%
of conventional medicine
because of their influence

00:02:49.380 --> 00:02:52.320 align:middle line:90%
on our so-called physical body.

00:02:52.320 --> 00:02:55.810 align:middle line:84%
However, there is a
different use for energy.

00:02:55.810 --> 00:02:58.830 align:middle line:90%
Energy is also information.

00:02:58.830 --> 00:03:01.448 align:middle line:84%
So, for example, the
cell phone broadcasts

00:03:01.448 --> 00:03:03.240 align:middle line:84%
that are going through
this room right now,

00:03:03.240 --> 00:03:05.310 align:middle line:84%
well, they don't
exhibit much force.

00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:07.560 align:middle line:84%
But they do carry a
lot of information.

00:03:07.560 --> 00:03:08.850 align:middle line:90%
Television signals?

00:03:08.850 --> 00:03:11.670 align:middle line:90%
Not forceful, but information.

00:03:11.670 --> 00:03:14.150 align:middle line:90%
So the idea is this.

00:03:14.150 --> 00:03:17.270 align:middle line:84%
Yes, the force
element of energy is

00:03:17.270 --> 00:03:20.360 align:middle line:84%
covered by conventional
allopathic medicine.

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:22.520 align:middle line:84%
But what about the
function of energy

00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:24.600 align:middle line:90%
that deals with information?

00:03:24.600 --> 00:03:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Interestingly enough, that
is with the primary subject

00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:31.250 align:middle line:84%
of complementary and
integral medicine,

00:03:31.250 --> 00:03:33.620 align:middle line:84%
bringing in energy
fields, consciousness,

00:03:33.620 --> 00:03:36.380 align:middle line:90%
and thought into our world.

00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:37.940 align:middle line:84%
And so it becomes
important for us

00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:42.200 align:middle line:84%
to recognize that
information as energy

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:47.030 align:middle line:84%
is profoundly important in
shaping who and what we are.

00:03:47.030 --> 00:03:49.970 align:middle line:84%
We have two perceptions now
about what controls biology--

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:53.750 align:middle line:84%
physical things, such as
drugs, or energy fields.

00:03:53.750 --> 00:03:56.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's interesting
because a physicist

00:03:56.540 --> 00:03:59.900 align:middle line:84%
by the name of McClare at
the University of London

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:04.730 align:middle line:84%
wanted to identify, is
signaling using chemistry

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:09.020 align:middle line:84%
more effective or less
effective than using signals

00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:11.402 align:middle line:90%
provided by energy?

00:04:11.402 --> 00:04:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's a
profound difference

00:04:12.860 --> 00:04:16.610 align:middle line:84%
in which type of source of
information is being used,

00:04:16.610 --> 00:04:20.279 align:middle line:84%
chemistry or energy
fields, for this reason.

00:04:20.279 --> 00:04:23.360 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps you might remember,
when you were in chemistry class

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:25.460 align:middle line:84%
early in your
school history, you

00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:28.190 align:middle line:84%
mixed a couple of
components in a test tube.

00:04:28.190 --> 00:04:30.620 align:middle line:84%
And you held that test
tube, and you felt the heat

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:32.790 align:middle line:90%
coming from that test tube.

00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:34.460 align:middle line:84%
It's called the
heat of reaction.

00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:37.070 align:middle line:90%
It's a thermochemical coupling.

00:04:37.070 --> 00:04:39.890 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well, what's
significant about that?

00:04:39.890 --> 00:04:44.420 align:middle line:84%
By definition, heat
is wasted energy.

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:48.830 align:middle line:84%
So significance is, when
you use a chemical or a drug

00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:53.000 align:middle line:84%
to carry information, when
that chemical or drug binds

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:59.480 align:middle line:84%
to another chemical in the body,
according to McClare, up to 98%

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:02.030 align:middle line:84%
of the available energy
of a chemical drug

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:05.540 align:middle line:84%
is actually dissipated
and wasted as heat.

00:05:05.540 --> 00:05:09.020 align:middle line:84%
In contrast, energy
signals don't give off

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:11.180 align:middle line:90%
thermochemical reactions.

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:15.080 align:middle line:84%
Energy signals are
almost 100% transferred

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:18.740 align:middle line:84%
between the source and the
receptor of that energy.

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:20.300 align:middle line:90%
There is no loss.

00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:23.780 align:middle line:84%
So according to
McClare, quantum physics

00:05:23.780 --> 00:05:27.650 align:middle line:84%
reveals that, in biology,
energy vibration signals

00:05:27.650 --> 00:05:30.560 align:middle line:84%
would undoubtedly be selected
over chemical signals

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.470 align:middle line:90%
in controlling our behavior.

00:05:33.470 --> 00:05:35.640 align:middle line:90%
Well, what is the actual role?

00:05:35.640 --> 00:05:39.360 align:middle line:84%
How do we know that energy
vibration is that important?

00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:41.700 align:middle line:84%
In a more recent study
in the journal "Nature,"

00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:44.390 align:middle line:84%
one of the most prestigious
journals on the planet,

00:05:44.390 --> 00:05:47.040 align:middle line:84%
there's an interesting article
by two authors, Pophristic

00:05:47.040 --> 00:05:48.120 align:middle line:90%
and Goodman.

00:05:48.120 --> 00:05:51.630 align:middle line:84%
I love the title, because
science is like the church.

00:05:51.630 --> 00:05:53.700 align:middle line:84%
We put into Latin, and
nobody knows what the heck

00:05:53.700 --> 00:05:54.960 align:middle line:90%
we're talking about.

00:05:54.960 --> 00:05:56.790 align:middle line:90%
So listen to this title.

00:05:56.790 --> 00:05:59.520 align:middle line:84%
"Hyperconjugation
not steric repulsion

00:05:59.520 --> 00:06:03.090 align:middle line:84%
leads to the staggered
structure of ethane."

00:06:03.090 --> 00:06:04.900 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:06:04.900 --> 00:06:06.620 align:middle line:90%
Well, it means simply this.

00:06:06.620 --> 00:06:10.380 align:middle line:84%
Ethane molecules twist
and rotate as molecules.

00:06:10.380 --> 00:06:12.960 align:middle line:90%
They twist and rotate.

00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:14.640 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, what's
the relevance?

00:06:14.640 --> 00:06:18.930 align:middle line:84%
It is the same process that
proteins use to create life.

00:06:18.930 --> 00:06:20.550 align:middle line:90%
And here's the point.

00:06:20.550 --> 00:06:23.550 align:middle line:84%
Science is based
on predictability.

00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And what Pophristic and
Goodman wanted to do

00:06:26.940 --> 00:06:31.290 align:middle line:84%
was predict the movement from
ethane's primary structure

00:06:31.290 --> 00:06:34.930 align:middle line:84%
and all the intermediate
stages as the ethane manifests

00:06:34.930 --> 00:06:36.690 align:middle line:90%
its secondary structure.

00:06:36.690 --> 00:06:38.300 align:middle line:84%
And if you can
predict the movements,

00:06:38.300 --> 00:06:40.133 align:middle line:84%
then you would understand
the mechanism that

00:06:40.133 --> 00:06:41.490 align:middle line:90%
provides for those movements.

00:06:41.490 --> 00:06:46.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, they started off using the
principles of Newtonian physics

00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:49.890 align:middle line:84%
to try to identify the
intermediate stages

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.660 align:middle line:90%
of the ethane structure.

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:52.770 align:middle line:90%
Guess what?

00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:56.580 align:middle line:84%
They were unable to predict
those intermediate stages.

00:06:56.580 --> 00:06:58.140 align:middle line:90%
Point is very clear.

00:06:58.140 --> 00:07:00.330 align:middle line:84%
The movement of
that ethane molecule

00:07:00.330 --> 00:07:05.520 align:middle line:84%
was not using Newtonian
physics in the process.

00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:09.750 align:middle line:84%
So they then applied quantum
mechanical principles

00:07:09.750 --> 00:07:12.150 align:middle line:90%
to the same ethane molecule.

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:15.390 align:middle line:84%
And in so doing, they were
able to accurately predict

00:07:15.390 --> 00:07:18.330 align:middle line:84%
all the intermediate
stages of that molecule

00:07:18.330 --> 00:07:22.040 align:middle line:84%
from its original shape
to its secondary shape.

00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:25.580 align:middle line:84%
The significance is profound,
because basically what it says

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:30.350 align:middle line:84%
is the movement of molecules,
the same as the movement

00:07:30.350 --> 00:07:34.160 align:middle line:84%
of proteins that create
life, are actually

00:07:34.160 --> 00:07:38.150 align:middle line:84%
regulated by quantum
physical principles

00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:40.910 align:middle line:90%
and not Newtonian principles.

00:07:40.910 --> 00:07:44.060 align:middle line:84%
The significance of
this was actually

00:07:44.060 --> 00:07:48.500 align:middle line:84%
spelled out in an editorial
in the very same journal

00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:50.270 align:middle line:90%
of "Nature."

00:07:50.270 --> 00:07:52.550 align:middle line:90%
The editorial's title I love--

00:07:52.550 --> 00:07:55.730 align:middle line:84%
"A new twist on
molecular shape."

00:07:55.730 --> 00:07:59.000 align:middle line:84%
The author, Frank
Weinhold, writes

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.530 align:middle line:90%
this in the introduction.

00:08:00.530 --> 00:08:02.180 align:middle line:84%
"What are the
forces that control

00:08:02.180 --> 00:08:06.140 align:middle line:84%
the twisting and folding of
molecules into complex shapes?"

00:08:06.140 --> 00:08:07.635 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's a good question.

00:08:07.635 --> 00:08:09.260 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why
it's a good question

00:08:09.260 --> 00:08:12.510 align:middle line:84%
is because that's the mechanism
where life comes from.

00:08:12.510 --> 00:08:15.470 align:middle line:84%
So if we could understand the
forces that provide for that,

00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:18.740 align:middle line:84%
then we can understand the
forces that provide for life.

00:08:18.740 --> 00:08:21.410 align:middle line:84%
Frank Weinhold goes
on to say, "Don't

00:08:21.410 --> 00:08:25.923 align:middle line:84%
look for the answers in your
organic chemistry textbook."

00:08:25.923 --> 00:08:27.590 align:middle line:84%
That sounds a little
cryptic, but here's

00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:29.510 align:middle line:90%
what's important about it.

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:33.320 align:middle line:84%
Conventional medicine is
based on the principles

00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:35.669 align:middle line:90%
in organic chemistry.

00:08:35.669 --> 00:08:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And what Weinhold
is saying is, if you

00:08:37.880 --> 00:08:41.000 align:middle line:84%
want to understand how
life works, don't look

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.990 align:middle line:84%
in that textbook, because
organic chemistry is predicated

00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:48.110 align:middle line:84%
on Newtonian physics
and does not understand

00:08:48.110 --> 00:08:50.300 align:middle line:84%
the relevance of
the quantum physics

00:08:50.300 --> 00:08:52.430 align:middle line:84%
in controlling the
character of life.

00:08:52.430 --> 00:08:56.420 align:middle line:84%
So the belief in
materialism that we've

00:08:56.420 --> 00:08:58.460 align:middle line:84%
been talking about
as the foundation

00:08:58.460 --> 00:09:02.720 align:middle line:84%
of the current culture, which
is scientific materialism,

00:09:02.720 --> 00:09:03.950 align:middle line:90%
is flawed.

00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:05.030 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:09:05.030 --> 00:09:09.350 align:middle line:84%
Because the idea of
materialism, a Newtonian idea,

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:12.950 align:middle line:84%
is not valid in a
quantum physical world,

00:09:12.950 --> 00:09:15.930 align:middle line:84%
the one in which we
are living right now.

00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:19.280 align:middle line:84%
So basically it says we
have to understand life

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:21.390 align:middle line:90%
from a different perspective.

00:09:21.390 --> 00:09:25.830 align:middle line:84%
And so I show you this picture
of two atoms interacting.

00:09:25.830 --> 00:09:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Our conventional
understanding is two atoms

00:09:27.770 --> 00:09:31.250 align:middle line:84%
come together, have a
collision, and, in that process,

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:33.350 align:middle line:90%
create chemistry.

00:09:33.350 --> 00:09:36.380 align:middle line:84%
But that is a
Newtonian illusion.

00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And so if you want to
understand how atoms interact

00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:42.110 align:middle line:84%
to create life, we
have to understand

00:09:42.110 --> 00:09:44.030 align:middle line:90%
the nature of energy waves.

00:09:44.030 --> 00:09:48.410 align:middle line:84%
And so, instead of seeing atoms
as individual particles, what

00:09:48.410 --> 00:09:52.700 align:middle line:84%
we can look at is atoms
as the presence of waves.

00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:55.730 align:middle line:84%
When atoms interact,
it's the waves

00:09:55.730 --> 00:09:57.760 align:middle line:84%
that are interacting,
because there's

00:09:57.760 --> 00:09:59.180 align:middle line:90%
nothing physical in the atom.

00:09:59.180 --> 00:10:01.700 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's called
interference.

00:10:01.700 --> 00:10:04.640 align:middle line:84%
Where the ripples interact,
they create special patterns

00:10:04.640 --> 00:10:05.840 align:middle line:90%
of interference.

00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:10.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, the interference of
these atoms are the ripples.

00:10:10.430 --> 00:10:12.830 align:middle line:84%
But the ripples
constitute the field.

00:10:12.830 --> 00:10:14.660 align:middle line:84%
And the field is
the invisible energy

00:10:14.660 --> 00:10:18.590 align:middle line:84%
of ripples of energy surrounding
all of us at all times.

00:10:18.590 --> 00:10:20.630 align:middle line:90%
Also recognize this.

00:10:20.630 --> 00:10:24.980 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness, thought, is
an expression of the field.

00:10:24.980 --> 00:10:29.300 align:middle line:84%
And then I emphasize
Albert Einstein's quote.

00:10:29.300 --> 00:10:31.370 align:middle line:90%
The field-- the energy--

00:10:31.370 --> 00:10:34.910 align:middle line:84%
is the sole governing
agency of the particle--

00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:36.980 align:middle line:90%
particle being matter.

00:10:36.980 --> 00:10:39.470 align:middle line:84%
And that changes how
we look, because it's

00:10:39.470 --> 00:10:42.410 align:middle line:84%
been left out of our
understanding of science.

00:10:42.410 --> 00:10:43.940 align:middle line:84%
And to try to get
an understanding

00:10:43.940 --> 00:10:47.600 align:middle line:84%
of how complex this
is, imagine seeing

00:10:47.600 --> 00:10:49.705 align:middle line:90%
raindrops fall on a pond--

00:10:49.705 --> 00:10:51.080 align:middle line:84%
and not looking
at the raindrops,

00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:53.580 align:middle line:84%
but looking at all the ripples
that come from the raindrops.

00:10:53.580 --> 00:10:56.780 align:middle line:84%
So, for a moment, consider
the raindrop as an atom,

00:10:56.780 --> 00:10:58.760 align:middle line:84%
and the ripples it's
generating are going

00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:00.710 align:middle line:90%
across the surface of the pond.

00:11:00.710 --> 00:11:02.840 align:middle line:90%
Look at the complex interaction.

00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:04.520 align:middle line:90%
Everything is interconnected.

00:11:04.520 --> 00:11:08.330 align:middle line:84%
All the waves from all the
